141вҶ’// в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ
142вҶ’// autoMatchExercises
143вҶ’// в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ
144вҶ’
145вҶ’/**
146вҶ’ * Normalize an exercise name for fuzzy matching:
147вҶ’ * - Lowercase
148вҶ’ * - Strip non-alphanumeric characters (spaces, hyphens, punctuation)
149вҶ’ * - Strip a trailing 's' (basic singular/plural normalisation)
150вҶ’ */
151вҶ’function normalizeName(name: string): string {
152вҶ’  return name
153вҶ’    .toLowerCase()
154вҶ’    .replace(/[^a-z0-9]/g, "")
155вҶ’    .replace(/s$/, "");
156вҶ’}
157вҶ’
158вҶ’/**
159вҶ’ * Attempt to automatically match our exercise templates to Hevy exercise
160вҶ’ * template IDs using normalized title comparison. Supports partial matching
161вҶ’ * (one normalized name contains the other).
162вҶ’ *
163вҶ’ * Returns a Map of our template ID вҶ’ Hevy template ID for every template
164вҶ’ * that could be matched.
165вҶ’ */
166вҶ’export function autoMatchExercises(
167вҶ’  ourTemplates: ExerciseTemplate[],
168вҶ’  hevyTemplates: HevyExerciseTemplate[]
169вҶ’): Map<string, string> {
170вҶ’  const result = new Map<string, string>();
171вҶ’
172вҶ’  // Pre-normalize Hevy template titles
173вҶ’  const normalizedHevy = hevyTemplates.map((t) => ({
174вҶ’    id: t.id,
175вҶ’    norm: normalizeName(t.title),
176вҶ’  }));
177вҶ’
178вҶ’  for (const template of ourTemplates) {
179вҶ’    const normOurs = normalizeName(template.title);
180вҶ’
181вҶ’    // Prefer exact match first
182вҶ’    let matched = normalizedHevy.find((t) => t.norm === normOurs);
183вҶ’
184вҶ’    // Fall back to partial match (one contains the other)
185вҶ’    if (!matched) {
186вҶ’      matched = normalizedHevy.find(
187вҶ’        (t) => t.norm.includes(normOurs) || normOurs.includes(t.norm)
188вҶ’      );
189вҶ’    }
190вҶ’
191вҶ’    if (matched) {
192вҶ’      result.set(template.id, matched.id);
193вҶ’    }
194вҶ’  }
195вҶ’
196вҶ’  return result;
197вҶ’}
